

## Overview
This repository contains the complete analysis for the Introduction to Quantitative Methods course assessment, focusing on two main studies:
1. Corruption and Municipal Health Councils in Brazil
2. Peace Index Analysis and Treatment Effects Study

## Technical Skills Demonstrated
- Statistical Analysis
  - Linear Regression Models
  - Difference-in-Differences (DiD) Analysis
  - T-tests and Hypothesis Testing
  - Confidence Interval Calculation
- Data Visualization
  - Box Plots
  - Treatment Effect Visualization
  - Statistical Plots using ggplot2
- R Programming
  - Data Manipulation
  - Statistical Modeling
  - Results Reporting

## Project Structure
### Corruption Analysis
- Municipal health council age impact on corruption
- Multi-variable regression analysis
- Interaction effects study

### Peace Index Study
- Treatment effect analysis
- Balance checks
- DiD estimation

## Key Packages Used
```r
library(ggplot2)    # Data visualization
library(textreg)    # Regression analysis
library(stargazer)  # Statistical reporting
library(sjPlot)     # Plot models
```

## Key Findings
1. Corruption Analysis:
   - Relationship between council age and corruption indices
   - Impact of poverty and reelection on corruption levels

2. Peace Index Study:
   - Treatment effects on peace index
   - Temporal changes in peace indicators
   - Statistical significance of findings

## Repository Navigation
- `/data`: Contains the datasets used in the analysis
- `/analysis`: R scripts for statistical analysis
- `/results`: Generated figures and tables
- `/docs`: Detailed methodology and analysis description

## Statistical Methods Applied
1. Linear Regression Analysis
2. Multiple Regression Models
3. Interaction Effects Analysis
4. Difference-in-Differences Estimation
5. Balance Testing
6. Confidence Interval Calculations

## Getting Started
```r
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/[your-username]/quantitative-methods-portfolio.git

# Install required packages
install.packages(c("ggplot2", "textreg", "stargazer", "sjPlot"))

# Run analysis scripts
source("analysis/01_corruption_analysis/corruption_regression.R")
source("analysis/02_peace_index_analysis/peace_analysis.R")
```

